FILE OUT NOTE - weighted participants: This is a proportional scaling of block participants so that the sum of block weighted participants == the total source participants. Required for Explore overview graph because participants aren't mutually exclusive, but the number of participants in an outer layer can't be more than the parent. Hence we scale it down.
FILE OUT NOTE 1 - ages: Age quartiles are calculated as the average over the 10 closest data points to the quartile index, rounded to 1 dp.
FILE OUT NOTE - totals & <10: when a non-zero <10 is encountered, we replace the value with <10 and round the total up as if the value was contributing 10
